  "texts": [
    "In more detail, the Center and Full models evaluate the impact of low LLM adaptability on the LLMs' prediction error.",
    "Low adaptability, i.e.",
    "the tendency of LLM answers to be similar across socio-demographics, implies a concentration around a central answer distribution.",
    "We operationalize this by computing, for each LLM-question pair, the LLM average answer distribution.",
    "This average is computed on a random subset of 20 subpopulations, a subset subsequently held out of the regression models so as to lift suspicions of endogeneity."
  ],
